## Premises

### County Hall, Atlantic Wharf, Cardiff

The council's main offices are at [County Hall](/County_Hall,_Cardiff) on Atlantic Wharf. It was built in 1987 as the headquarters of the former [South Glamorgan County Council](/South_Glamorgan_County_Council). The council also uses the [City Hall](/City_Hall,_Cardiff) on Cathays Park in the city centre, built in 1906 for the former [Cardiff City Council](/Cardiff_County_Borough_Council). Full council meetings were held at County Hall prior to 2020, when the [COVID-19 pandemic](/COVID-19_pandemic) required meetings to be held virtually. From the resumption of in-person meetings in May 2022, full council meetings were held at City Hall. City Hall closed for refurbishment in 2023 but is planned to be brought back into use as the council's meeting place once the work is complete, although this may not be until 2026.

